No action has been taken yeton the Reagan Adminstration's offer to escort Kuwaiti oiltankers through the Gulf, but the issue is being discussed,U.S. Secretary of Defence Caspar Weinberger said.    The offer was made to Kuwait in light of Iran's deploymentof Chinese-built missiles to cover the entrance to the Gulf.    Weinberger told reporters prior to a speech at TexasChristian University that he did not think Iran and the UnitedStates were moving towards a potential conflict, adding thatthe Straits of Hormuz at the mouth of the Gulf were still "freewater." REUTER&#3;